MA Seminar in Literary Theory II supports and monitors the writing of the Master's thesis and offers both the specialized and the interdisciplinary forum for discussion. The MA students of curricula Literature and Theatre Research and European Languages and Cultures who are writing their theses in literature are expected to participate in this seminar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the Master's seminar is to support the writing of the Master's thesis and to offer both the specialized and the interdisciplinary forum for discussion.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The seminar directs the student to work systematically with his/her Master's thesis, to plan and organize it, to learn to ask research questions and to choose theoretical/methodological approach and the volume of the work according to them. The supervisor of the thesis takes also part in the work of the seminar.
